<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>St Matthew CCD</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <main class="container py-5 app-shell">
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-end gap-2 mb-3">
      <span class="text-secondary"><%= t('language') %>:</span>
      <a href="/lang/en" class="btn btn-sm <%= lang === 'en' ? 'btn-primary' : 'btn-outline-primary' %>"><%= t('english') %></a>
      <a href="/lang/es" class="btn btn-sm <%= lang === 'es' ? 'btn-primary' : 'btn-outline-primary' %>"><%= t('spanish') %></a>
    </div>

    <section class="hero p-4 p-md-5 mb-4">
      <h1 class="display-6 fw-bold brand-title mb-2"><%= t('app_title') %></h1>
      <p class="lead mb-1"><%= t('landing_focus_title') %></p>
      <p class="mb-0"><%= t('landing_focus_subtitle') %></p>
    </section>

    <div class="card page-card">
      <div class="card-body p-4">
        <h3 class="h5 mb-3">Faith Formation at St. Matthew Parish</h3>
        <p>At St. Matthew Catholic Church, faith formation is more than a program—it is a journey of growing as disciples of Jesus Christ. Our parish seeks to help children, parents, and families deepen their relationship with Christ and live their Catholic faith in everyday life.</p>
        <p>Inspired by the vision of Family Faith Formation Catholic Ministries, St. Matthew Parish embraces a family-centered approach to faith formation, recognizing parents as the first and most important teachers of the faith.</p>
        
        <div class="accordion" id="faithFormationAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                A Family-Centered Vision
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#faithFormationAccordion">
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Faith is best learned and lived within the family. For this reason, our parish faith formation model encourages parents and children to grow in faith together.</p>
                <p>Rather than seeing religious education as only a classroom experience for children, St. Matthew Parish supports families by providing:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Formation opportunities for both parents and children</li>
                  <li>Resources to help families practice and discuss their faith at home</li>
                  <li>Parish gatherings that foster prayer, learning, and community</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This approach reflects the Church’s teaching that the family is the “domestic church,” where the faith is first experienced and shared.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                Parish and Family Working Together
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faithFormationAccordion">
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Faith formation at St. Matthew Parish is a partnership between the parish community and the family. Our parish supports parents by providing guidance, catechetical resources, and opportunities for formation throughout the year.</p>
                <p>Families participate in:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Periodic family catechesis gatherings</li>
                  <li>Sacramental preparation programs</li>
                  <li>Opportunities for prayer, fellowship, and service</li>
                  <li>Faith-centered activities that strengthen family life and community bonds</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Through this partnership, the parish accompanies families as they grow together in faith.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                Sacramental Preparation
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faithFormationAccordion">
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Preparation for the Sacraments—especially First Reconciliation, First Holy Communion, and Confirmation—is an important part of our faith formation process.</p>
                <p>Parents are actively involved in preparing their children to receive these sacraments. Through retreats, parish sessions, and home-based formation, families are invited to deepen their understanding of the sacraments and grow in their relationship with Christ.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
                Growing as Missionary Disciples
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faithFormationAccordion">
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>The goal of faith formation at St. Matthew Parish is not only to teach about the faith but to form missionary disciples who live the Gospel.</p>
                <p>Through prayer, catechesis, community life, and service, we strive to help our parish community:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Develop a personal relationship with Jesus Christ</li>
                  <li>Grow in love for Sacred Scripture and the Sacraments</li>
                  <li>Experience the support of the parish community</li>
                  <li>Live the Gospel through service and witness</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Faith formation is a lifelong journey, and St. Matthew Parish is committed to accompanying individuals and families at every stage of that journey.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <hr>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-3"><%= t('secure_online') %></p>
        <% if (user) { %>
          <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 align-items-center">
            <span class="badge text-bg-primary badge-role"><%= user.role %></span>
            <span class="text-secondary"><%= t('signed_in_as') %> <strong><%= user.email %></strong></span>
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/dashboard"><%= t('open_dashboard') %></a>
            <a class="btn btn-success" href="/registration/new"><%= t('register_child') %></a>
            <a class="btn btn-info" href="/registration/adult"><%= t('register_adult') %></a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary" href="/logout"><%= t('logout') %></a>
          </div>
        <% } else { %>
          <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/signup"><%= t('create_account') %></a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-primary" href="/login"><%= t('login') %></a>
          </div>
        <% } %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
